Roger Maxwell (1 January 1900 – 24 November 1971) was an English actor.On stage he appeared in the West End in Ian Hay's Leave It to Psmith and Off the Record, Terence Rattigan's Who Is Sylvia? and Peter Jones's The Party Spirit
In 1959, he was a member of the jury at the Venice Film Festival.Maxwell was born and died in London, England.
